[Here's a patch with a test.  The test fails without the code changes and demonstrates that a Writer that checks whether it has been closed will cause a problem with the current code.

There are a number of ways to fix this, I simply added a configuration step that checks if any of jackson's JsonFactory features are configured, and in turn configures them for the DelegationTokenAuthenticationHandler.  This lets you specify arbitrary jackson features, which is nice, but it does have some risk in terms of feature names changing.  Alternatively, you could define a static mapping from features to auth handler configs, or allow the user to pass in a JsonFactory to init (although the code currently casts everything to String, so that would have to change)., | (x) *{color:red}-1 overall{color}* |
